	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=148087><span id= >WarriorOne</span></a><br><span id=notbold>456 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.30]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>All I've got to say is this...<br><br>I'm a Warrior.&nbsp;&nbsp;I don't have uber gear.  I don't have the resouces available to get to alot of the uber gear.  This cloak is better than the one I'm currently using.  If it drops, I don't care if there are 20 Monks in my friggin group, I'm rolling for it.<br><br>In KC, got into a Warlord group.  We had a Monk puller.  Tranq Staff dropped, we gave it to the Monk (a total stranger, the rest of the group was friends of mine).  We didn't roll, even though that single staff could've bought me all the gear I wanted.  I saw a Monk in EC the other day offering 100kpp in cash and items for one a Tranq Staff.  I do the same with all loot that drops.  If someone needs it and I don't, I won't roll against them.  How many groups would've just given up a Tranq Staff?  Not many.  So if something drops and I need it, you can be damn sure I'm rolling.  I don't care if it has 0.0 weight and 200 mana on it.  If it has better stats than what I got, I need it.  Someone else needs it, they can stick around until it drops and roll, too.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=678568 target=akztarg>Khuan Scorpse</a><br>Scourge Knight of Cazic Thule<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1145935 target=akztarg>Sumana Scorpse</a><br>Rabbitslayer of Karana<br><a href=HTTP://www.7thhammer.net target=akztarg>7th Hammer</a> - <a href=HTTP://www.thedarkexile.com target=akztarg>The Dark Exile</a></td></tr>
